### Understand VERCEL_URL Environment Variable (TypeScript)

Source: https://github.com/vercel/vercel/blob/main/packages/functions/docs/modules/index.md

This environment variable provides the domain name of the generated deployment URL, excluding the protocol (e.g., https://). Note that this variable cannot be used with Standard Deployment Protection. The example shows a wildcard domain.

```typescript
"*.vercel.app"
```

--------------------------------

### Create deployment and stream events (JavaScript)

Source: https://github.com/vercel/vercel/blob/main/packages/client/README.md

Call createDeployment and iterate emitted events with a for-await-of loop to observe deployment progress and capture the ready payload. Inputs: an options object containing token and path (and optional teamId or other deployment fields). Output: the deployment payload when an event of type 'ready' is received. Limitations: path must refer to files on the same level and a valid Vercel token is required.

```JavaScript
async function deploy() {
  let deployment;

  for await (const event of createDeployment({
    token: process.env.TOKEN,
    path: '/Users/me/Code/myproject',
  })) {
    if (event.type === 'ready') {
      deployment = event.payload;
      break;
    }
  }

  return deployment;
}
```

